According to DHS, Awad has a history of violence since entering the U.S. in 2017 through the [Diversity Visa program](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/immigration/illegal-immigrants).

He was previously charged with [domestic violence](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/crime/police-and-law-enforcement), intimidation, possession of a weapon, violation of a court order and vehicle theft, the agency said.

"Horrendous immigration policies allowed this monster into our country and made victims of children and families," Assistant Secretary Tricia McLaughlin said in a statement. "This child rapist was allowed into our country by the Diversity Lottery program. Secretary Noem paused the diversity lottery to ensure no more Americans are harmed by this disastrous program."

