McLaughlin added that ICE's arrest detainer would "ensure he is not released onto our streets to victimize more children."

According to DHS, the victim called her sister, who then contacted authorities after Awad left the residence.

Awad was later apprehended by police in Louisville, [Kentucky](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/us-regions/southeast/kentucky), on Jan. 16, and was extradited to Tennessee the following week.

He was charged with [aggravated rape](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/crime/rape) with a weapon, aggravated assault with a deadly weapon and aggravated burglary, DHS said.

